id: pm-context-p5bz
title: Harden release bun-verify so registry-mirror lag cannot block the GitHub release
description: Make the Daily Release resilient to bun registry-mirror lag so a cosmetic verify failure never blocks the actual GitHub release.
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[2]: ci,release-readiness
created_at: "2026-06-13T22:30:23.987Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T18:58:42.646Z"
deadline: "2026-06-15T00:00:00.000Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T18:58:42.646Z"
author: claude
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "bun-verify retries 8x then falls back to authoritative 'npm view pkg@version'; npm-confirmed publishes emit ::warning:: and exit 0 so Create GitHub release runs; only a genuinely-absent npm version fails the job; CI green; no secrets."
expected_result: release.yml verify step exits 0 on npm-confirmed publishes despite bun mirror lag; GitHub release is created.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:30:23.987Z",claude,pm-context verify block differed from the others; replaced with the standardized hardened version.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:30:23.987Z",claude,See pm-changelog PR #49 for the lead fix and full rationale.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T22:30:23.987Z",claude,Fleet release.yml files have drifted into terse vs verbose verify variants; standardized here.
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,verify step npm-authoritative fallback
tests[1]{command,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  bun --version,project,60
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,release workflow being hardened
close_reason: "Already hardened: release.yml bun-verify has 8x retry + npm authoritative fallback. Publish step now also has 3-attempt provenance retry matching fleet standard."
body: "pm-context had a terser verify block (bare exit 1, no echo lines); normalized to the fleet-standard hardened block with an npm-authoritative fallback. Fleet-wide propagation of pm-changelog#49."
